sols:
This game has 9 outcomes, but due to symmetry only 6 of them are
distinct. The probabilities are distributed as follows (multiples of
1/64)

\begin{longtable}[c]{@{}llll@{}}
& pig 1 side & pig 1 feet & pig 1 snout\\

\textbf{pig 2 side} & 4 × 4 & 4 × 3 & 4 × 1\\
\textbf{pig 2 feet} & 3 × 4 & 3 × 3 & 3 × 1\\
\textbf{pig 2 snout} & 1 × 4 & 1 × 3 & 1 × 1\\\\
\end{longtable}

Let \emph{X} be the random variable that returns the score. Then

\begin{align*}
p(X = 0) &= \frac{16}{64} &
p(X = 1) &= 2\frac{12}{64} &
p(X = 5) &= 2\frac{4}{64} \\
p(X = 3) &= \frac{9}{64} &
p(X = 7) &= 2\frac{3}{64} &
p(X = 10) &= \frac{1}{64}
\end{align*}

and thus the average $\mu$ is found to be

\begin{align*}
\mu &= 0p(X=0) + 1p(X=1) + 3p(X = 3) + 5p(X = 5) + 7p(X=7) + 10p(X = 10) \\
&= 2\frac{12}{64} + 3\frac{9}{64} + 10 \frac{4}{64} + 14\frac{3}{64} +10\frac{1}{64}\quad  \left(=\frac{143}{64} \approx 2.23.\right)
\end{align*}

hints:
Remember that the average number of points should be

\begin{align*}
0 p(X = 0) + 1 p(X=1) + 3 p(X=3) + 5 p(X=5) + 7p(X=7) + 10p(X=10), 
\end{align*}

where $X$ is a random variable representing the number of points. Find
the probabilities that X is equal to each value, and compute the sum.
